added.title: Who Is The Red Poncho?
added.description: Craig and his friends seek to unmask the mysterious villain who is messing with their search for the Heart of the Forest.

added.title: The Once And Future King
added.description: The former King of the Other Side of the Creek shares his story.

added.title: Sheep Bears
added.description: The Bears get jobs as sheep herders on an idyllic farm.

added.title: Ice Bear's Pet
added.description: Ice Bear attempts to keep a giant owl-monster secretly as a pet.

added.title: Dragon Pests
added.description: The Bears and Squatter Otter crash a couple's swanky pad while they're out of town.

added.title: Squirrels Squirrels Squirrels
added.description: Courtney's attempt to make Chef a better teacher fails when a squirrel gets his hands on her mind-control device.

added.title: Say Hello to my Little Friends
added.description: After telling the kids he will not miss them over the long weekend Chef locks himself into the school and finds out he was very, very wrong.

added.title: WaterHose-Five
added.description: The hottest day of the year and a broke air conditioner leads to a water battle of epic proportions to determine who controls the garden hose.

added.title: Cody the Barbarian
added.description: Cody is set to inherit a video game empire from his long lost uncle, but only if he and his friends have what it takes to conquer a fantastical live action video game.

added.title: TP2: Judgement Bidet
added.description: When the city experiences a toilet paper shortage Beth and Harold investigate and discover it's their old rival Sewer Mike who is the mastermind behind it all.

added.title: Pardon the Garden/Put the Cat Out: Flat on the Door/Downward Duck
added.description: Petunia Pig wants to garden, but all she grows is trouble! Sylvester is a-door-able. Yoga is relaxing - unless Daffy is your instructor.

added.title: Lesson Plan 9 from Outer Space/ Balloon Salesman: Baboon/ Portal Kombat
added.description: Marvin the Martian has conquered Earth… but no one bothered to tell Bugs. Daffy Duck becomes a balloon salesman. Wile E. Coyote uses sci-fi portals to catch Roadrunner.

added.title: Forgeti
added.description: When Gwen drags Ben along on a hike in search of the legendary Forgeti, a yeti that makes people forget they ever saw it, Ben is dubious. But with Dr. Animo on the trail of the mythical beast as well, what looks like a hoax becomes a hero time adventure for the ages, if Ben can remember it ever happened.

added.title: Max to the Max
added.description: While Ben, Gwen, and Max hike to a waterfall, the Bugg Brothers are back with a plan to duplicate Diamondhead; but when their cloning ray gun fires on Max instead, multiplying him endlessly, Gwen and Ben must round up all the Maxes while also fighting off the Bugg Brothers.

added.title: Cutting Corners
added.description: Ben approaches Geezer Bob about doing a little yard work to earn spending money, but when Ben goes Upgrade to transform the lawnmower into a super fast mowing machine, he accidentally draws the ire of Bob's gnome-neighbors, the tiny, terrifyingly tenacious Billy-Bob Goblins.

added.title: Xingo
added.description: Ben is more interested in a marathon of his favorite cartoon show, "Xingo", but when Ben goes Upgrade to get a better signal, the titular Xingo leaps from his animated dimension to ours, bringing mad chaos with him!

added.title: Scared Silly
added.description: When the Rust Bucket runs out of gas on a foggy East Coast road, Ben, Gwen and Max are forced to stay at a hotel being menaced by Creepy Carl, a local folklore expert, who may actually be a ghost!

added.title: Ultimate Weapon
added.description: When Max finds out that part of an alien weapon has been unearthed in Texas, he becomes obsessed with finding it. In doing so, he leads Ben and Gwen on a wild adventure.

added.title: Tough Luck
added.description: Gwen's Lucky Girl powers return when she buys a magical stone at a magic convention in Las Vegas. However, Hex is after the same stone, and after his niece breaks him out of prison, the two set off to retrieve the stone.

added.title: They Lurk Below
added.description: Max's old friend has built the world's only underwater resort, and Ben, Gwen and Max are invited for a sneak peak. But it turns out in order to power the resort, Max's friend took an energy orb from a race of underwater aliens. Now, the aliens want their energy orb back and destroy the resort in order to get it.

added.title: Dr. Animo and the Mutant Ray
added.description: Dr. Animo has broken out of jail, and has been tracking down Ben, intent on revenge. At the same time, Ben's broken off a piece of the Omnitrix, and as a result, has turned into weird alien combinations, i.e. StinkArms.

added.title: Back with a Vengeance
added.description: Ben's feeling cocky with the watch. He's unlocked its secret, and now can become any alien he wants, whenever he wants. That's the good news. The bad news is, after finding one another in the depths of space, Kevin 11 and Vilgax have teamed up and have returned to earth to destroy Ben and get the Omnitrix.

added.title: Olvideti
added.description: Ben, Gwen y Max van de excursión en busca de un Forgeti legendario, un yeti que hace que las personas se olviden de que lo vieron, pero cuando el Doctor Ánimo reúne a los Forgeti para su plan de robar bancos sin que nadie los recuerde, Ben aprende muy pronto que el Forgeti es más que un simple mito.

added.title: Max Al Maximo
added.description: Mientras Ben, Gwen y Max van de excursión a una cascada, los Hermanos Bugg regresan con el plan de duplicar a Diamante. Pero cuando su arma láser clonadora le dispara a Max por error-y lo multiplica infinitamente-, Gwen y Ben deben juntar a todos los Maxes y ahuyentar a los Hermanos Bugg a la vez.

added.title: Cortando Camino
added.description: Ben habla con Geezer Bob para hacer alguna tarea de jardín y así ganar un poco de dinero, pero cuando Ben se transforma en Upgrade para convertir la podadora de césped en una cortadora súper rápida, por accidente despierta la ira de los vecinos gnomos de Bob: los diminutos y aterradoramente obstinados duendes de Billy Bob.

added.title: Xingo
added.description: Ben está muy interesado en una maratón de Spazz, su dibujo animado favorito, pero cuando se transforma en Upgrade para mejorar la señal de televisión, el protagonista de Spazz salta de su dimensión animada hacia la nuestra...iy trae consigo un caos demente!

added.title: Muerto De Miedo
added.description: Cuando la Chatarra se queda sin gasolina en una carretera brumosa de la Costa Este, Ben, Gwen y Max se ven obligados a pasar la noche en un hotel amenazado por Creepy Carl, iun experto en folclore de la zona que podría ser un fantasma verdadero!

added.title: When You're A Jet
added.description: Green Arrow and his Arrowplane, Goldie, come to help Batman take on the Riddler. Batwing is so happy to have another flying vehicle around that she brings Goldie to life and the two become BFFs. But when Goldie eventually has to leave, Batwing learns that saying goodbye doesn't always mean forever!

added.title: Ride Along
added.description: After Kitty the Catmobile saves Bam when he's in a tight spot, Bam decides to take her on a ride along patrol in the hopes of recruiting her as a Batwheel if he can convince her to stop playing long enough to focus on their mission!

added.title: Bright Light
added.description: When Mayor Foghorn Leghorn hires The Looney Builders to build a lighthouse for Looneyburg, Lola's tablet breaks and she must rely on herself.

added.title: Moo-ving Day!/Follow That Breeze
added.description: Zee's growth ray turns Moobert giant, but when a storm rolls in, the Mechas need to build a shelter big enough to fit her./After Ranger Nat's kite blows away in the wind, the Mechas and Timmy learn to build their own kite to find it.

added.title: Cross That Bridge/Knock Knock! Who's There?
added.description: The train needs to cross the ravine, which becomes difficult when the Martians accidentally break the bridge./The Zee Mobile is great at counting the chickens at the farm, but won't stop crashing into and ruining MacBarm's barn door.

added.title: Bear Hibernation
added.description: Blippi wonders how do bears prepare for hibernation?

added.title: Snowy Excavator Song
added.description: A special animated music video episode to the tune of Blippi's new "Snowy Excavator" Song.

added.title: Christmas Scavenger Hunt
added.description: Blippi wonders what is the best part about Christmas?

added.title: Blippi Saves Christmas
added.description: Blippi wonders how does Santa know where we live?

added.title: Penguins
added.description: Blippi wonders can penguins fly?

added.title: Fruity Ice Cream
added.description: It's a hot day so Woolly Sheep sets up an ice cream stall outside Lellobee City Farm. Ella, Rishi, Lettie and Carlos bring Woolly fresh apples, oranges, bananas and cherries from the farm so Woolly can make them delicious and refreshing fruity ice cream.

added.title: 10 Little Buses
added.description: It's a sunny day and Ella is having fun drawing pictures of the buses of Lellobee City Farm! Help Ella count all of the buses as they drive by!

added.title: Five Little Ducks
added.description: Ella, Mama Duck and the five little ducklings are having a game of Hide and Seek. The ducklings hide all around the farm - on Heidi's hat, in the vegetable patch, on a hay bail, on Carlo's guitar and among some flowers. Will Ella and Mama Duck be able to find them?!

added.title: The Five Senses Shakedown
added.description: Ella is feeling a little bit anxious. Fortunately her Grandma has taught her a mindfulness exercise. Ella takes us around the farm to find five things to see, four things to feel, three things to hear, two things to smell and one thing to taste. By the end of the song Ella feels happier and calmer.

added.title: Father's Day
added.description: It's Father's Day and to celebrate there's BBQ at the farm. Ben and Izzy are there with their Dads. Ella's Dad can't attend, but that doesn't stop Ella joining in with all the fun.
